Explore Navbar Automation

This module automates the Explore section of the application using Selenium with Python and follows the Page Object Model (POM) design pattern.

The ExploreNavbar class contains locators and methods to interact with the Explore navigation menu and validate user navigation through different sections.

Features Covered
Click on the Explore menu from the navigation bar
Select a specific country (Vietnam) from the dropdown
Navigate to a travel package (Escape to Vietnam)

Implementation Details
Uses Explicit Waits (WebDriverWait) for reliable interaction
Implements Selenium Expected Conditions for element visibility and clickability
Follows Page Object Model (POM) for better code structure and reusability

Class Overview
click_explore() → Opens the Explore menu
click_countrys() → Selects the country (Vietnam)
click_packages() → Opens the selected package


This feature ensures that:

Navigation through the Explore section works correctly
Users can select destinations and view related packages without issues